{"tid":1757040,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"［國際文宣，廣傳］有鬼佬拍片，控訴中共揾人攝錄投票人士容貌，干預選舉","createTime":"2019-11-26T10:21:56.000Z","updateTime":"2019-11-26T11:36:10.000Z","uid":48083,"like":10,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":8,"replies":[{"pid":"2c256277a19b5df3dbf4be165b740f6f88ca9029","tid":1757040,"uid":48083,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-26T10:21:56.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/HeDmG9P.png\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FHeDmG9P.png&h=4ae8f26a&s={SIZE}\" /><a href=\"https://m.facebook.com/hkalleys/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fm.facebook.com%2Fhkalleys%2F&d=AiROHBMCWVTnLPrCQVkx9wDrJ99PsHpDQ3gYSBhgLgU%3D&h=1a0f9617\" target=\"_blank\">https://m.facebook.com/hkalleys/</a>"},{"pid":"65588c5f2ba10b33d5def7f95ba453ed3f431e22","tid":1757040,"uid":48083,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-26T10:25:03.000Z","msg":"另外極推介share哩篇文<br />\n清楚講咗香港選舉既各種舞弊問題<br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/n4O9Q4h.png\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2Fn4O9Q4h.png&h=9f707b68&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\nThese interesting claims ⋯⋯neglecting common measures adopted by themselves that have been observed in past Hong Kong elections. A few examples include:-<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Planting votes&rdquo;: personal information, especially the elderly and disabled, are used to register ghost voters that do not exist. Investigation journalism revealed that an apartment contained 13 residents with 7 surnames.<br />\n<br />\nCoaches are broadly used to carry elderly and people that appear to be coming from mainland to cast votes for particular candidates.<br />\n<br />\nThis year a video clip showing an elderly in wheelchair was instructed by volunteers of a candidate to vote for him, whereas the elderly herself appeared to be unaware of what she was going to do, not to mention who that candidate was.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Gifts&rdquo; such as pillows and large bags of rice were given out to &ldquo;members&rdquo; of some associations that had casted their votes. One of the organisers was found to be an advocate of bringing more mainland Chinese to &ldquo;re-unite&rdquo; with their &ldquo;relatives&rdquo; in Hong Kong.<br />\n<br />\nOfficers at polling stations were seen to be biased when judging questionable votes, often favourable to pro-establishment candidates.<br />\n<br />\nThe government required candidates to declare their loyalty to the &ldquo;one-country, two systems&rdquo; framework, thereby screening out those pro-independence candidates. Joshua Wong, the face of the &ldquo;Umbrella Revolution&rdquo;, was banned from running for the election this year after the authority ruled he did not pass the test.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://medium.com/賴叔睇育/4-things-that-weve-learnt-from-hong-kong-s-local-elections-598efe5689e3\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2F%E8%B3%B4%E5%8F%94%E7%9D%87%E8%82%B2%2F4-things-that-weve-learnt-from-hong-kong-s-local-elections-598efe5689e3&d=AiROHBMCWVTnLPrCQVkx9wDrJ99PsHpDQ3gYSBhgLgU%3D&h=41dd042b\" target=\"_blank\">https://medium.com/賴叔睇育/4-things-that-weve-learnt-from-hong-kong-s-local-elections-598efe5689e3</a>"},{"pid":"613c61c4c951022bbea262809cf49d278795d25d","tid":1757040,"uid":90183,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-26T10:27:41.000Z","msg":"Cap 低晒所有人個樣再俾AI data <br />\nCls<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dislike.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dislike.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dislike.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill2.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill2.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill2.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"40233fb09fa95f10240093dd9b79e3a1e6f40785","tid":1757040,"uid":249263,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTim